A lorry driver has been arrested on suspicion of dangerous driving in connection with the death of a man who was killed as he cycled alongside a busy dual carriageway.

The driver, who is in his forties, was arrested and taken into custody after a collision on the A38 near Plymouth, Devon, yesterday morning.

The 58-year-old cyclist, who is local to the area, suffered serious injuries and was flown to Derriford Hospital, where he later died from his injuries.

